HEADWORD: Roundfish
<hw>Round"fish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any ordinary market fish, exclusive of flounders,
sole, halibut, and other <xex>flatfishes</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A lake whitefish (<spn>Coregonus quadrilateralis</spn>), less
compressed than the common species. It is very abundant in British
America and Alaska.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

